{"id":446930,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brigade","text":"=\"preserve\">A brigade is a military unit in an army. Currently in most armies, a brigade is made up of several battalions. Up to World War II, a brigade had several regiments.\nA brigade is commanded by a brigadier general, a brigadier, or a colonel.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Military_organization","surface_form":"military unit","offset":27},{"uri":"Army","surface_form":"army","offset":47},{"uri":"Battalion","surface_form":"battalion","offset":111},{"uri":"World_War_II","surface_form":"World War II","offset":129},{"uri":"Regiment","surface_form":"regiment","offset":165},{"uri":"Brigadier_general","surface_form":"brigadier general","offset":204},{"uri":"Brigadier","surface_form":"brigadier","offset":225},{"uri":"Colonel","surface_form":"colonel","offset":241}]}